# Claude Code — Top 20 Most Helpful Shortcuts
# Reference this file anytime with: cat .tmp

## Built-in Slash Commands

| Command        | What it's for |
|----------------|---------------|
| /init          | Scans your project and creates CLAUDE.md with project context, conventions, and structure — run this first in any new repo |
| /compact       | Summarizes and compresses conversation history to free up context window space without losing session continuity |
| /cost          | Shows token usage and estimated cost for the current session |
| /clear         | Wipes the conversation entirely and starts fresh — more aggressive than /compact |
| /resume        | Resumes a previous Claude Code session by reloading its context |
| /summary       | Generates a concise summary of what has been done in the current session |
| /context       | Shows the current context window state — what's loaded, how full it is |
| /memory        | Opens your memory file (CLAUDE.md or project memory) for review and editing |
| /model         | Switches the active model (e.g., swap to Opus 4.6 for harder reasoning tasks) |
| /fast          | Toggles fast mode — same Opus 4.6 model but optimized for faster output throughput |
| /help          | Lists all available commands and keyboard shortcuts |
| /doctor        | Diagnoses Claude Code environment issues (auth, config, MCP servers, etc.) |
| /vim           | Toggles vim keybindings in the input editor |

## Superpowers Skills (invoked as /skill-name or via the Skill tool)

| Command         | What it's for |
|-----------------|---------------|
| /plan           | Writes a detailed, step-by-step implementation plan before touching code — prevents rework |
| /review         | Full code review against the plan and coding standards after completing a feature or step |
| /security-review| Security-focused review checking for OWASP top 10, injection flaws, auth issues, etc. |
| /brainstorm     | Explores intent, requirements, and design space before implementing anything creative or complex |
| /tdd            | Enforces test-driven development workflow — write tests first, then implementation |
| /debug          | Systematic debugging process — diagnose root cause before proposing fixes |
| /loop           | Runs a command or prompt on a recurring interval (e.g., /loop 5m /review) |

## Keyboard Shortcuts

| Shortcut      | Action |
|---------------|--------|
| Ctrl+C        | Cancel the current running operation |
| Escape        | Cancel input / interrupt |
| Up/Down       | Navigate command history |
| Ctrl+R        | Search previous commands |
| Shift+Enter   | Insert a newline without submitting |

## Pro Tips
- Run /init once per project, then /plan before any multi-step feature
- Use /compact aggressively to keep context window healthy in long sessions
- /cost before /compact lets you track spend per task
- /brainstorm → /plan → implement → /review is the golden workflow
